{"data":[{"type":"questionAttempts","id":"17599093","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/questionAttempts/17599093"},"attributes":{"position":0,"marks":1,"score":0,"answeredAt":"2025-09-30T11:50:08+09:30","options":[1],"response":null,"finalizedAt":"2025-09-30T11:50:08+09:30"},"relationships":{"user":{"data":{"type":"users","id":"50098"}},"questionSession":{"data":null},"session":{"data":null},"question":{"data":{"type":"questions","id":"15528"}},"bookmark":{"data":null}}}],"included":[{"type":"questions","id":"15528","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/questions/15528"},"attributes":{"optionProportions":[0.11,0.14,0,0,0.76]},"relationships":{"item":{"data":{"type":"items","id":"8219"}},"activeRevision":{"data":{"type":"questionRevisions","id":"61745"}}}},{"type":"items","id":"8219","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/items/8219"},"attributes":{"contentType":"question"},"relationships":{"content":{"data":{"type":"questions","id":"15528"}},"activeRevision":{"data":{"type":"itemRevisions","id":"47191"}},"tags":{"data":[{"type":"tags","id":"67"},{"type":"tags","id":"71"},{"type":"tags","id":"74"},{"type":"tags","id":"4929"},{"type":"tags","id":"4941"},{"type":"tags","id":"4942"},{"type":"tags","id":"4949"},{"type":"tags","id":"5189"},{"type":"tags","id":"5322"},{"type":"tags","id":"7004"},{"type":"tags","id":"7607"},{"type":"tags","id":"9877"},{"type":"tags","id":"10095"},{"type":"tags","id":"10146"},{"type":"tags","id":"10592"}]},"contributions":{"data":[{"type":"contributions","id":"19879"},{"type":"contributions","id":"19882"},{"type":"contributions","id":"22346"}]}},"meta":{"canRevise":false,"canManage":false,"canDelete":false}},{"type":"questionRevisions","id":"61745","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/questionRevisions/61745"},"attributes":{"stem":"\u003Cp\u003EThe pituitary gland consists of two distinct lobes with different embryological origins and functions.\u003C/p\u003E","stemQuestion":"Which one of the following hormones is released by the anterior pituitary gland?","responseType":"sba","marks":1,"options":["Oxytocin","Vasopressin","Melatonin","Progesterone","Prolactin"],"correctOptions":[4],"correctResponses":null,"explanation":"\u003Cp\u003EThe anterior and posterior pituitary have different embryological origins and secrete different hormones. \u003Cstrong\u003EOxytocin\u003C/strong\u003E and \u003Cstrong\u003Evasopressin\u003C/strong\u003E are synthesized in the hypothalamus but stored and released by the posterior pituitary. \u003Cstrong\u003EMelatonin\u003C/strong\u003E is produced by the pineal gland and regulates circadian rhythms. \u003Cstrong\u003EProgesterone\u003C/strong\u003E is primarily produced by the corpus luteum during the menstrual cycle and by the placenta during pregnancy.\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003EProlactin\u003C/strong\u003E is one of six hormones produced and released by the anterior pituitary. The others are growth hormone, thyroid-stimulating hormone, adrenocorticotropic hormone, follicle-stimulating hormone, and luteinizing hormone.\u003C/p\u003E","optionExplanations":["","","","",""],"learningPoints":["The anterior pituitary releases prolactin, while the posterior pituitary stores and releases oxytocin and vasopressin","Melatonin is produced by the pineal gland","Progesterone is primarily produced by the corpus luteum and placenta"],"references":["Melmed, S., Polonsky, K. S., Larsen, P. R., \u0026 Kronenberg, H. M. (2015). Williams textbook of endocrinology E-Book. Elsevier Health Sciences. Kovacs, W. J., \u0026 Ojeda, S. R. (Eds.). (2012). Textbook of endocrine physiology. OUP USA.","Melmed, S., Polonsky, K. S., Larsen, P. R., \u0026 Kronenberg, H. M. (2015). Williams textbook of endocrinology E-Book. Elsevier Health Sciences.","Serri O, Chik CL, Ur E, Ezzat S. Diagnosis and management of hyperprolactinemia. CMAJ. 2003 Sep 16;169(6):575-81. PMID: 12975226; PMCID: PMC191295."]},"relationships":{"itemRevision":{"data":{"type":"itemRevis